  • Method Details

    • getNewFeed

      public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getNewFeed()
      Creates a object of type `Feed` and call method `readFeed` from `RSSFeedParse` with parameter of `0` meanning not all messages, and we get only 1 new feed. It is added to result list, as a string using method `toString` and added to `oldEntries` (marked as read)
      Returns:
      a List of String that represent some feeds

    • addFeed

      public void addFeed​(java.lang.String url) throws java.lang.Exception
      Try to add the url to the listened feeds and throws an exception if can't
      Parameters:
      url - a String that represent the url to the feed, that is get through a "GET" request to the url
      Throws:
      java.lang.Exception - - can't load url

    • markAsRead

      public void markAsRead​(int allFeeds, int index)
      Or parse all feeds and add them to `oldEntries`(mark as read) Or get only a feed, and add to `oldEntries` olny that entire feed
      Parameters:
      allFeeds - type int, represent that we add to `oldEntries` all the feeds or not
      index - type int, represent the position in `parsers` of feed

    • removeFeed

      public java.lang.String removeFeed​(java.lang.String s)
      Remove a link from listened feeds by a string as general as possible, and return what link has been removed
      Parameters:
      s - type String, `value`
      Returns:
      returns the url's feed in succes case, and if not, the message
